<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-08-19T03:25:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-08-19T03:25:00-05:00" n="659" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d659">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">884.6461 Tsana Dam/434:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ethiopia (<persName type="from">Southard</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Addis Ababa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-08-19T11:00:00+02:35">August
                                        19, 1933—11 a.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received August 20—7:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Please inform White Engineering Corporation that I just now have
                                possession of the Egyptian check for $159,153 endorsed to them and
                                will mail at once.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Southard</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>